      "In a single-loop generator, the induced EMF is a direct result of the rate at which the conductor is 'cutting magnetic flux'.",
      "The timing of the sine-wave (Periodic Time and Frequency) is determined by how quickly the loop completes its 360-degree rotation.",
      "To understand the full AC system, we must link the physical rotation of the machine to the mathematical values of the resulting wave."
    ],
    "questionText": "Imagine you are monitoring a single-loop generator. If the mechanical speed of the rotor is doubled, explain the specific impact this has on the resulting sine-wave's Peak voltage and its Frequency. In your answer, explain the technical reason for both changes based on flux cutting and periodic time.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "Peak Voltage: Doubling the speed increases the rate of cutting magnetic flux, which induces a higher EMF, resulting in a higher (doubled) Peak voltage.",
      "Frequency: Doubling the speed halves the Periodic Time (T) because the loop completes a cycle faster; since f = 1/T, this results in a doubled Frequency (Hz)."
    ],
    "hint": "Think about how 'rate of change' affects voltage and how 'time per cycle' affects the number of cycles in one second."
  }
